The District Governor of the Rotary Club, Mr Ayo Oyedokun, wants philanthropists in the country to support the less privileged in a bid to build a virile nation. Mr Ayo Oyedokun stated this in Bwari, Abuja when the Rotary Club Bwari handed over an accommodation to the Bwari General Hospital as part of the effort to support the health care delivery services in the FCT. Police arrest 2 robbers, recover arms in Ekiti Insecurity: OPSH trains 975 vigilantes in Southern Kaduna He said the accommodation was meant for mothers whose babies are on admission to the neo-natal intensive care. The President of the Bwari Rotary District, Mrs Bukola Britto-Jatto, who commended the efforts of Bwari General Hospital in providing good health care facilities for the people of Bwari and its environs, said the gesture was part of their social responsibility. Responding, the Chief Medical Director of Bwari General Hospital, Dr Anate Abdullahi, while appreciating the gesture, said the support was gratifying and assured the Rotary Club of proper utilisation of the building for the maximum benefit of patients. Dr Anate also thanked the Federal Capital Territory Administration for its support of the general hospital.